<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<section xml:id="activity-1-12-data" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Activity: Collecting Data</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>Before beginning Investigation 1.12, you will collect a sample. Enter the class ID provided by your instructor below to access the data collection tool.</p>
  </introduction>

  <exercise xml:id="data-collection-1-12">
    <title>Enter Your Class ID</title>
    <statement>
      <p>Enter your class ID (provided by your instructor) and click Go to access the data collection tool:</p>
      
      <interactive xml:id="class-id-input" platform="html">
        <slate xml:id="class-id-slate" surface="html">
          <![CDATA[
          <div style="padding: 20px; background-color: #f5f5f5; border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 5px;">
            <label for="classIdInput" style="font-weight: bold; margin-right: 10px;">Class ID:</label>
            <input type="text" id="classIdInput" placeholder="e.g., chancesec1" 
                   style="padding: 8px; width: 250px; font-size: 14px; border: 1px solid #ccc; border-radius: 3px;"/>
            <button onclick="navigateToDataCollection()" 
                    style="padding: 8px 20px; margin-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; background-color: #4CAF50; color: white; border: none; border-radius: 3px; cursor: pointer;">
              Go
            </button>
          </div>
          <script>
            function navigateToDataCollection() {
              var classid = document.getElementById('classIdInput').value;
              if (classid && classid.trim() !== '') {
                var url = 'https://www.rossmanchance.com/gettysburgDataCollection.html?instructor=' + encodeURIComponent(classid.trim());
                window.open(url, '_blank');
              } else {
                alert('Please enter a class ID');
              }
            }
            // Allow Enter key to submit
            document.getElementById('classIdInput').addEventListener('keypress', function(event) {
              if (event.key === 'Enter') {
                navigateToDataCollection();
              }
            });
          </script>
          ]]>
        </slate>
      </interactive>
      
      <p><alert>Important:</alert> After the data collection tool opens, select 10 representative words from the Gettysburg Address passage and submit them. Then copy your list of words - you will need to paste them in Investigation 1.12 on the next page.</p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>

</section>
